text: Carrasco Creek () is a Uruguayan stream, separating Canelones Department and Montevideo Department. It flows from the Carrasco Swamps into the Río de la Plata. It is one of the most contaminated water streams in the country. ==See also== *List of rivers of Uruguay ==References== ==External links== Category:Rivers of Uruguay Category:Rivers of Montevideo Department Category:Rivers of Canelones Department
